 HN31[
] An "oligopoly" is the "control or domination of a market by a few large sellers." Black's Law Dictionary (8th ed.). By 
definition, it results in "high prices." Id.

 § 401. Notice of copyright: Visually perceptible copies (a) HN11[
] General provisions. Whenever a work protected under this title is published in the United States or elsewhere by 
authority of the copyright owner, a notice of copyright as provided by this section may be placed on publicly distributed copies 
from which the work can be visually perceived, either directly or with the aid of a machine or device. (Emphasis added.)
